article.headline: Ress scores 20 for Eagles
article.linkText: BC gets plenty of Ress against Miami
article.story:
HARTFORD, Connecticut (Ticker) -- Kathrin Ress led all 
scorers with 20 points and helped Boston College (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) defeat No. 21 Miami 65-53 in a quarterfinal matchup of the Big East tournament.

Ress connected on seven of 10 shoots, nailed all six free throws
and pulled down seven rebounds for Boston College (23-6), which
on Monday will play the winner of Connecticut (No. 3 ESPN/USA Today, No. 4 AP) versus
Virginia Tech.

Jessalyn Deveny scored 17 points and Clare Droesch grabbed eight
rebounds for the Eagles, who led at halftime, 23-20.

Yalonda McCormick delivered 19 points, six assists and five
rebounds for Miami (22-6), which shot just 2-of-5 from the
free-throw line and 3-of-15 from three-point range.

Shaquana Wilkins led the Hurricanes with seven rebounds and
provided 12 points.
